config.playStoreFullDescription_EN_US:
This app is meant as a starting point for Health Authorities constructing their own Exposure Notifications Application.
It attempts to include best practices that Health Authority developers should following when building their apps.

config.testVerificationIntroMessage_EN_US:
{ Verification intro message; content provided by Public Health Authority.

Example Text: Help protect your community by sharing your diagnosis with your public health authority.

Your public health authority needs some information from you. They need this information to send notifications to people who may have been exposed.
 }
config.symptomsOnsetDescription_EN_US:
{ Verification - Symptom onset message; content provided by Public Health Authority

Example Text: Symptoms of COVID-19 can appear 2-14 days after exposure and include:

• Fever or chills
• Cough
• Shortness of breath or difficulty breathing
• Fatigue
• Muscle or body aches
• Headache
• New loss of taste or smell
• Sore throat
• Congestion or runny nose
• Nausea or vomiting
• Diarrhea
 }
